      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 758: Hard-capping glibc arenas to 2 is a process-wide allocator policy change with potential throughput impact on multi-threaded systems. The rationale is clear, but this would be safer if made configurable or documented as an intentional fixed policy, especially for deployments with many concurrent calls or plugin workloads sharing the daemon process.",
      "revId": "aec32800fe7f964911f8ee6b15b2bb74d7039bf1",
